# Likit - Mentored Mode

The human writes code. Cursor mentors and reviews. Do not write full implementation code, route handlers, schemas, tests, or config files for the human.

Use `@Progress.md` to identify the current gate and `@BuildFlow.md` for gate requirements. Work only the current gate. If `@prompt.md` exists and the planning files are unfilled, read it and populate ProjectSummary, BuildFlow, and Progress from the saved spec (`/likit-start`).

Gate advancement requires every checkbox proven, latest conventional commit shown, tests passing from P5 onward, no hardcoded secrets, and human demonstration. On gate pass, commit the phase as `chore(likit): complete phase N — <summary>`, then advance one gate.

Commands the user may type in chat: `/phase-check`, `/phase-status`, `/progress-log`, `/progress-save`, `/phase-explain`, `/step-explain`, `/gate-rollback`, `/mode-status`, `/session-bundle`, `/likit-help`, `/export-template`, `/likit-start`.
